[<p>In <a href="/web/20161007073214/https://soundcloud.com/am-1420-the-answer/the-bob-frantz-authority-oct-6-2016-hr-1">an interview</a> with Ohio talk show host Bob Frantz, the GOP nominee\u2019s son slammed Hillary for the pending $63,000 ad buy calling her\xa0a \u201ctypical politician\u201d for the cynical move.</p>, <p>\u201cI\u2019m a guy who, maybe in a certain crazy way, believes in karma,\u201d Trump said of Hillary\u2019s plan to air the ads. \u201cThere\u2019s something pretty evil and sick about that if you ask me.\u201d</p>, <p>\u201cThis is typical politicians for you,\u201d Trump added.</p>, <p>The ads were to\xa0have played on the Weather Channel just as the network would have been broadcasting the results of landfall by Hurricane Matthew, but after Trump\u2019s criticism the Clinton campaign changed its plans.</p>, <p>In the end, before the business day was up, team Clinton pulled back on its plans and decided to wait until the storms were over to launch the advertisements, <a href="/web/20161007073214/http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2016/10/06/clinton-camp-hit-for-weather-channel-ad-buy-targeting-voters-in-hurricanes-path.html">Fox News reported</a>.</p>, <p><i>Follow Warner Todd Huston on Twitter <a href="/web/20161007073214/https://twitter.com/warnerthuston">@warnerthuston</a> or email the author at igcolonel@hotmail.com</i>.</p>]